{
  "experiment": "D3_v2_KRAS_stratified -- Does structural position predict drug sensitivity within KRAS-dependent NSCLC lines?",
  "parent": "D3_NSCLC_v1 (5b60be0) -- DENIED across unselected NSCLC panel",
  "rationale": "D3_NSCLC_v1 failed (r=+0.036) due to three identified confounds: (1) MDM2 inhibitors require TP53-WT context (inactive in ~50-60% TP53-mut lines), (2) BET/MYC inhibitors have potency gap (partial transcriptional suppression insufficient), (3) MEK1 is pharmacologically effective in KRAS-mutant lines despite being a near-zero anchor. This experiment tests whether removing the context-gated nodes (MDM2, EGFR) and restricting to KRAS-dependent lines produces the ODS-consistent prediction. In KRAS-addicted cells, the PI3K/AKT/mTOR axis and MAPK axis are both constitutively active, providing a homogeneous signaling context for the test.",
