      "id": "h1",
      "statement": "Spearman r(delta-r, mean PRISM LFC) < -0.40 across 5 node-drug class pairs (mTOR, MYC, MEK1, PI3K, AKT1) within lung_NSC lines filtered to KRAS Chronos < -0.5. delta-r values as in D3_NSCLC_v1 pre-registration. Same -0.40 effect size threshold. n=5 pairs. If confirmed: ODS structural position predicts drug sensitivity within KRAS-dependent context, and D3_v1 failure was due to context-gating (MDM2) and cross-subtype averaging. If denied: structural position does not predict drug sensitivity even within a homogeneous oncogenic driver context."
    },
    {
      "id": "h2",
      "statement": "mTOR inhibitors (structural damper, delta-r=+0.049) will show more negative mean LFC than MEK1 inhibitors (structural anchor, delta-r=-0.011) within KRAS Chronos < -0.5 lines. This is the single most important pair-wise prediction: mTOR is the only confirmed damper with context-independent drug efficacy. MEK1 is the anchor with the best D3_v1 drug efficacy. If mTOR > MEK1 (more killing), ODS is correct for the two most informative nodes. If MEK1 > mTOR, the pharmacological bottleneck argument overrides structural position even in KRAS context."
